ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Ethereum transaction analysis is the process of monitoring and analyzing new transactions on the Ethereum blockchain. It allows you to track incoming and outgoing transfers, detect patterns, and gain insights into Ethereum activity.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_2: How can transaction analysis benefit me?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: Transaction analysis provides valuable intelligence for Ethereum users, developers, and businesses. It enables tracking of funds, identification of whale movements, detection of suspicious activity, and more.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: What data is included in the analysis?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: The analysis covers various transaction details such as sender, receiver, value transferred, gas fees, timestamp, and any associated data like smart contract calls. Insights are derived from this raw on-chain data.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: How often is the data updated?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: Our Ethereum transaction analysis is updated in real-time as new blocks are mined. This ensures you always have access to the latest on-chain activity and analytics.
FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get answers to common questions about our Ethereum transaction analysis app
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: Our app provides real-time analysis of new transactions on the Ethereum blockchain. It monitors the network, decodes incoming transactions, and provides insights into transaction details, smart contract interactions, and more.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: We run Ethereum nodes that connect to the network and stream transaction data as it arrives. Our proprietary algorithms then parse and analyze this data, extracting valuable intelligence that is displayed through our user interface.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: What kind of data is provided?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: The app shows transaction hashes, sent/received addresses, ether values, gas usage, success status, and involved smart contracts. For contract transactions, it decodes the input data to show the called function and parameters.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Yes, we provide a JSON-RPC API that allows programmatic access to our transaction data stream and parsed analytics. This enables integration into your own apps and services.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: We have a free tier for low usage, as well as paid monthly subscription plans that increase data rate limits and add enterprise features like dedicated nodes and SLA-backed uptime.
